vllm-gfx1201
============

This project packages and lightly extends a large body of other people's work.
It would not exist without the following. Please preserve this NOTICE and the
upstream licenses in any redistribution.

The ONLY original contributions in this repository are:
  - the gfx1201 (RDNA4) enablement edits to vLLM / aiter / flash-attention,
  - the Docker build/inject packaging and compose profiles, and
  - the W4A8-FP8-WMMA MoE kernel (w4a8_fp8_wmma/).
Everything else is upstream, credited below.

Upstream projects and people
----------------------------
- vLLM — vllm-project/vllm (Apache-2.0). The entire serving engine. Our gfx1201
  vLLM wheel is built from the ROCm/vllm fork's `micah/therock-nightly` branch;
  thanks to @micah and the ROCm vLLM team. Our changes are a small ROCm
  platform-enablement edit plus the moe_wna16 tp_size fix (a generic upstream
  bug — owed back as a PR).
- AMD ROCm / TheRock — the base image rocm/vllm-dev:nightly-therock714, the
  ROCm 7.14 SDK, and the torch/triton nightlies (various AMD/OSS licenses).
- AMD aiter — ROCm/aiter (MIT/Apache). Our aiter wheel is their tree plus
  gfx1201 enablement. The five A8W8 GEMM config JSONs come directly from
  @carhuang's `carhuang/gfx1201_silu_and_mul_and_a8w8_configs_rebased` branch.
- Dao-AILab flash-attention — Dao-AILab/flash-attention (BSD-3-Clause), and
  ROCm Composable Kernel (ROCm/composable_kernel, MIT) for the CK FMHA backend.
  Thanks to @tridao.
- tilelang — the Qwen3_5Moe linear-attention (MHC) kernel path (upstream
  integration PR #43679).
- @kyuz0 — prior gfx1201 vLLM / ROCm-on-RDNA4 containers and PRs (e.g. the ViT
  attention-backend fix) that informed this enablement.
- cyankiwi — the AWQ-INT4 quantized models we run and benchmark
  (Qwen3.6-35B-A3B-AWQ-4bit, Mellum2-12B-A2.5B). The Qwen team for the base
  models.
- The gfx1151 sibling project (vllm-awq4-qwen) — the repository structure,
  compose, and README template, and the RDNA3.5 wave32 kernel-design lineage the
  W4A8 kernel was scaffolded from.
